  "brightness": {
    "uuid": "2E4DBB0A-A950-4896-BC2D-A5B0CFF7FAC6", "pluginName": "PAEBrightness", "min_psnr": 32,
    "note": "PAEBrightness = HGColorMatrix diagonal (per-channel MULTIPLY), DECODED from -[PAEBrightness canThrowRenderOutput] @0xfcdd0 (setter@0x60 rows 0/1/2 = (b,0,0,0)/(0,b,0,0)/(0,0,b,0)). Darkening (b<1) matches headless as a plain sRGB multiply (PSNR 47). BRIGHTENING (b>1) DIVERGES (PSNR ~13): the headless transfer curve rolls off toward 255 (in50->149, in150->238 at b=1.5), which is neither an sRGB nor a linear-light multiply — it is the HGColorMatrix multiply composed with FCP's headless WORKING-SPACE encode/decode (a systemic color-pipeline issue shared by all filters, not a Brightness bug). No shipping transition brightens (all 27 users darken), so this is an unexercised-input ceiling; documented, not fit.",
    "cases": [
      {"label": "darken 0.5", "params": [{"name":"Brightness","id":1,"value":0.5}]},
